[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This video is an introduction to three major&nbsp; updates to LTX 2.3 video pipeline. The first&nbsp;&nbsp; updates are the releases of two LTX 2.3&nbsp; fine-tuned models. These are especially&nbsp;&nbsp; trained and tuned for NSFW generations.&nbsp; 10EROS is a fine-tuned variant based off&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of SULPHUR-2\'s data set and is more focused on&nbsp; image to video flows. Both need to be used in&nbsp;&nbsp; conjunction with the newly released Distill&nbsp; Laura in order to create better quality NSFW&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'contents. Here are the links to these files.&nbsp; Choose the one that is right for your current&nbsp;&nbsp; LTX 2.3 workflow. Here is the SULPHUR-2 repo and&nbsp; the files. There is also this SULPHUR Laura which&nbsp;&nbsp; you may want to experiment with, but for what I&nbsp; have tested, generations work better without it,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so I have not included it in this workflow. And&nbsp; if you click here, you will be able to download&nbsp;&nbsp; the distill LoRa required for the workflow.&nbsp; Also, you could use this link to get the same&nbsp;&nbsp; distill LoRa from another repo. Then here is the&nbsp; repo for the 10EROS variant. If you use KijAI\'s&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'LTX video template, choose the FP8 transformer&nbsp; model. I\'ll be using the full BF16 models with&nbsp;&nbsp; the recommended distill LoRa. The second&nbsp; update is the prompt relay node from KijAI.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This node provides users with a smart and easy&nbsp; way and enables us to specifically prompt each&nbsp;&nbsp; segments in the video timeline with a different&nbsp; scene or action. There actually two versions of&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the node. If you want to explore further, please&nbsp; have a read of the details provided in their repo. So let\'s have a look at this workflow. This is&nbsp; where we load our ref image and resize and rescale&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it to our desired resolution and aspect ratio.&nbsp; In this example, I rescaled the image into a 9x16&nbsp;&nbsp; ratio and then upscaled it further 1.5 times&nbsp; to feed into the pipeline. As per my beliefs,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the bigger the image, the cleaner the output. As&nbsp; for the actual video resolution, it will be set&nbsp;&nbsp; in the other nodes. Here I have added two base&nbsp; model loaders for testing both model variants,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the SULPHUR-2 and the 10EROS. Use this node to&nbsp; switch between the two. Per all my NSFW gen tests&nbsp;&nbsp; done earlier, I find that the 10os model gives&nbsp; me a much better consistency and quality output,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'although not 100%. I will show the comparison&nbsp; of my tests of regular DEV and NSFW variants&nbsp;&nbsp; for SFW content later. If you are not generating&nbsp; NSFW videos, I would suggest using the base dev&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'model with the regular distill LoRa. Then here are&nbsp; the VAE loaders, clip, and upscale model loaders.&nbsp;&nbsp; Bypass or delete this node if you are not planning&nbsp; to use a secondary GPU. And then the third update,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'VRGDG has released a set of very cool LoRas that&nbsp; I think you should check out and try. Here is the&nbsp;&nbsp; repo of VRGAMEDEVGIRL84 with lots of wonderful LTX&nbsp; 2.3 LoRas. All trigger words and usage details can&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'be found inside each LoRa\'s model cards. I have&nbsp; tested all of them and they work very well and&nbsp;&nbsp; very much as expected. And that is the reason I&nbsp; am creating this workflow to explore all three&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'updates at the same time. Here we load the distill&nbsp; LoRa and the VRVB LoRa. I am using this LoRa for&nbsp;&nbsp; better LTX reasoning when using larger prompts.&nbsp; I find that it sort of helps with my generation&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a lot. The LoRa is constantly being trained. So&nbsp; check out and try. And here we use the sampling&nbsp;&nbsp; preview node for gen preview while sampling. Here&nbsp; are the video gen control nodes. The T2I switch,&nbsp;&nbsp; width, height, length, and FPS. Okay. Next&nbsp; is our prompt relay node. Since I will not&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'do NSFW video testing, I will use the&nbsp; post-apocalyptic LoRa. So, I use this&nbsp;&nbsp; trigger word. The syntax I am using after a&nbsp; lot of tests with various types of formats,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I find that it works for me very well by starting&nbsp; my prompts with the frame number followed by&nbsp;&nbsp; the colon and then the prompts. I stuff the&nbsp; whole prompt into the global prompt section,&nbsp;&nbsp; then separate them into each segments below. Then&nbsp; I set the frame counts for each segment by either&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dragging them like so, or by entering&nbsp; the numbers in the length input below. Since my third prompt starts at frame number 240,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so I drag the handle and mash the numbers&nbsp; accordingly. If you want the length of the&nbsp;&nbsp; segments to be equally distributed,&nbsp; you can click the equalize button. Also remember to set the total video&nbsp; length in this field to match the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'length entered in the control node as&nbsp; mentioned earlier. I tried to link them,&nbsp;&nbsp; but this node won\'t update the numbers in&nbsp; real time, so I do it manually. Then next&nbsp;&nbsp; are the regular base and upscale sampler&nbsp; groups. And finally, the decoding nodes.'

[05:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Again, as mentioned in the dev\'s repo, this&nbsp; model was fine-tuned to work well with I2V gens,&nbsp;&nbsp; but still works with T2V flows. And per my&nbsp; testing output, they are not as good. But for&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the SULPHUR-2 model, both work pretty well on my&nbsp; rig. My verdict, for NSFW contents, I like 10EROS&nbsp;&nbsp; the most. But for SFW contents, it has got to be&nbsp; the full dev model with the distill LoRa only.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I recommend reading 10EROS repo for better&nbsp; understanding of how this model works. One&nbsp;&nbsp; thing to remember though is that you really need&nbsp; a very descriptive prompt. From my experiences,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'LTX tends to take shortcuts. It would be much&nbsp; better to describe each and every action in&nbsp;&nbsp; all prompts in detail. And that\'s it for this&nbsp; video. Thanks for watching and have a good one.'
